I've had a dream where privacy is a natural by-product, not a clumsy patch. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where social networks emerged from daily use, not from exchanging cards. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where I was able to be truly anonymous when I wanted to, but truly recognizable if I chose so. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where there were only a box in which to write, no matter if I was searching or publishing. It simply KNEW. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where standards were made to fit people, not people to adhere to standards. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where my information is MY information, not UGC subjected to TOS and EULAs. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where my thoughts were not broken in tiny pieces, but neatly organized though not centralized. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where I did not chase information down, but information flew to me. #webofdreams
I've had a dream where I did not tell my friends and family to sign up for the same online services I'm using. #webofdreams
